<P>
   LA-DEM-CONVEN (Los Angeles) _ Los Angeles is trying to lure the
Democratic National Convention to the city in 2000, but some
question whether L.A.'s strategy is powerful enough to win against
six other cities vying to play convention host. Boston Mayor Thomas
Menino is using gifts of coffee cakes and coffee table books,
arranged for fireworks to be set off inside his city's Fleet
Center, and made sure hockey great Bobby Orr offered the Democrats
drinks at a Red Sox game. The stakes are enormous. The winner will
host 30,000 guests who will generate an estimated $150million in
revenue. The 15,000 media members will give the host city's
attractions unparalleled publicity. By Rick Orlov.
