<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Where to call
 &HT;    By Mike Williams
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Visitors heading to Florida with children, the elderly or family
members who have heart or respiratory problems should call ahead to
check conditions if they plan to visit an area hit by fires and
smoke. Hardest-hit counties have been in northeast Florida from
Jacksonville to Daytona Beach. Visitors also might want to stop at
Florida Welcome stations to check on possible road closures or
detours due to smoke. Here are some numbers to call:
</P>
<P>
   _ Florida Tourism Information: 1-888-246-8728.
</P>
<P>
   _ Volusia County Tourism Information: 1-800-544-0415.
</P>
<P>
   _ Florida Department of Transportation: 1-800-749-2967 (in
Florida); 904-758-3700 (out of state).
</P>
<P>
   _ Florida Welcome stations:
</P>
<P>
   I-75: Jennings, near Georgia border.
</P>
<P>
   I-95: Yulee, near Georgia border.
</P>
<P>
   I-10: Pensacola, near Alabama border.
</P>
<P>
   U.S. 231: Campbellton, near Alabama border.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
