   NBA-LABOR _ A new labor agreement is not expected by the July 1
deadline, so the NBA effectively will shut down. No rookie camps,
no signings, no trades until an agreement is reached. We explain
the reason for this labor strife and look at how long it could
continue. (Bunn, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
