<SLUG> BC-AZR-BUDGET-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
The Arizona Republic plans to move the following stories for use by
clients of the NYTimes News service for Sunday, June 28. If you
have any questions, please call the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
TILLMAN (Phoenix) _ Oscar Tillman has a file folder full of death
threats. He doesn't worry about the ones that come to his office,
which he stashes and locks in a cabinet. It's the ones that find
their way to his home that disturb him. Those, he complains,
violate a sacred division between his kick- down-the-door,
in-your-face public persona - and a gentle private life devoted to
his family. Tillman is the state's NAACP president and a part-time
minister. He talks like a drill sergeant and has made the Valley
his boot camp. By Julie Amparano. Story will move in the ``A''
category.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
MONTINI-COLUMN (Phoenix) _ Every time one of them Eastern dandies
does a report on us, they make it out like all us in Arizona is
``ranchers and rodeo hands.'' Well, we ain't. We's also rustlers
and gunslingers, desperadoes and cutthroats, thieves, cattle
rustlers, and all pertinent forms of brainless, toothless,
gun-totin' maniacs. By E.J. MONTINI. Story will move in the ``A''
and ``K'' categories. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
